//revision from js 

---> map()
1] The map() method creates a new array with the results of calling a function for every array element.

2] The map() method calls the provided function once for each element in an array, in order.

3] Note: map() does not execute the function for array elements without values.

3] Note: this method does not change the original array.

---->indexof()
1] The indexOf() method searches the array for the specified item, and returns its position.

2] Returns -1 if the item is not found.

3] If the item is present more than once, the indexOf method returns the position of the first occurence.

---->filter()

1] The filter() method creates an array filled with all array elements that pass a test (provided as a function).

2] Note: filter() does not execute the function for array elements without values.

3] Note: filter() does not change the original array.


